== Records ==

=== Historical Chronicles ===
The ''{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'', in its entry for the 13th year of [[Emperor Tenmu]] (684), lists these six clans—Kamitsukeno no Kimi, Kuramochi no Kimi, Shimotsukeno no Kimi, Sami no Kimi, Ōno no Kimi, and Ikeda no Kimi—among the 52 clans granted the Rank of {{ill|Ason|ja|朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} under the {{ill|Eight Rank System|ja|八色の姓|1=Eight Kabane system|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (八色の姓).

The ''{{ill|Shoku Nihongi|ja|続日本紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'', in its entry for the 10th year of [[Enryaku]] (791), states that the Ikebara clan and Kamitsukeno clan traced their lineage to {{ill|Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It further explains that the descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto, referred to as the "Azuma no Kuni Mutsu Hara no Ason," were granted their surnames and clan names based on their residences.

The ''{{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'', in its entry for the 1st year of [[Gangyō]] (877), mentions that the Kamitsukeno, Ōno, Ikeda, Sami, and Kuramochi clans all share a common ancestry as descendants of [[Emperor Sujin]].

=== Shinsen Shōjiroku ===
In the early [[Heian period]], the ''{{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'' (compiled in 815) lists the following clans as part of the same imperial lineage:
* {{ill|Right Capital Kamitsukeno no Ason|ja|右京 上毛野朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto, the son of [[Emperor Sujin]]<ref>There is also a Kamitsukeno no Ason listed under the Left Capital, but this belongs to the Tanabe-no-Fumi lineage and is unrelated to the Azuma no Kuni Mutsu Hara.</ref>
* {{ill|Left Capital Shimotsukeno no Ason|ja|左京 下毛野朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto, the son of Emperor Sujin
* {{ill|Right Capital Ōno no Ason|ja|右京 大野朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Descendants of {{ill|Aratawake|ja|大荒田別命|Aratawake=Aratawake|lt=Ōaratawake-no-mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the fourth-generation descendant of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto
* {{ill|Left Capital Ikeda no Ason|ja|左京 池田朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Same lineage as Kamitsukeno no Ason; descendants of Sada-kimi, the tenth-generation descendant of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto
* {{ill|Right Capital Sami no Ason|ja|右京 佐味朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Same lineage as Kamitsukeno no Ason; descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto
* {{ill|Left Capital Kuramochi no Ason|ja|左京 車持公|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Same lineage as Kamitsukeno no Ason; descendants of Isasa-kimi, the eighth-generation descendant of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto

