'''Azuma no Kuni Mutsu Hara no Ason''' (東国六腹朝臣) refers to a collective term for the following six clans, all of which claim common origins in the [[Keno Province]] area:
* {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Ason (Kamitsukeno clan)|ja|上毛野朝臣（上毛野氏）|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno no Ason (Kamitsukeno clan)|qq=}} * {{ill|Shimotsukeno clan|ja|下毛野朝臣（下毛野氏）|Shimotsukeno clan=Shimotsukeno clan|lt=Shimotsukeno no Ason (Shimotsukeno clan)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimotsukeno clan|qq=}} * {{ill|Ōno no Ason (Ōno clan)|ja|大野朝臣（大野氏）|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōno no Ason (Ōno clan)|qq=}} * {{ill|Ikeda no Ason (Ikeda clan)|ja|池田朝臣（池田氏）|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikeda no Ason (Ikeda clan)|qq=}} * {{ill|Sami no Ason (Sami clan)|ja|佐味朝臣（佐味氏）|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sami no Ason (Sami clan)|qq=}} * {{ill|Kuramochi no Ason (Kuramochi clan)|ja|車持朝臣（車持氏）|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuramochi no Ason (Kuramochi clan)|qq=}}
== Records ==
=== Historical Chronicles === The ''[[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]'', in its entry for the 13th year of [[Emperor Tenmu]] (684), lists these six clans—Kamitsukeno no Kimi, Kuramochi no Kimi, Shimotsukeno no Kimi, Sami no Kimi, Ōno no Kimi, and Ikeda no Kimi—among the 52 clans granted the Rank of [[:en:Ason|Ason]] under the {{ill|Eight Rank System|ja|八色の姓|1=Eight Kabane system|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Rank System|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Kabane system|qq=}} (八色の姓).
The ''[[:en:Shoku Nihongi|Shoku Nihongi]]'', in its entry for the 10th year of [[Enryaku]] (791), states that the Ikebara clan and Kamitsukeno clan traced their lineage to {{ill|Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=}}. It further explains that the descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto, referred to as the "Azuma no Kuni Mutsu Hara no Ason," were granted their surnames and clan names based on their residences.
The ''[[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]'', in its entry for the 1st year of [[Gangyō]] (877), mentions that the Kamitsukeno, Ōno, Ikeda, Sami, and Kuramochi clans all share a common ancestry as descendants of [[Emperor Sujin]].
=== Shinsen Shōjiroku === In the early [[Heian period]], the ''[[:en:Shinsen Shōjiroku|Shinsen Shōjiroku]]'' (compiled in 815) lists the following clans as part of the same imperial lineage: * {{ill|Right Capital Kamitsukeno no Ason|ja|右京 上毛野朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Right Capital Kamitsukeno no Ason|qq=}} - Descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto, the son of [[Emperor Sujin]]<ref>There is also a Kamitsukeno no Ason listed under the Left Capital, but this belongs to the Tanabe-no-Fumi lineage and is unrelated to the Azuma no Kuni Mutsu Hara.</ref> * {{ill|Left Capital Shimotsukeno no Ason|ja|左京 下毛野朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Left Capital Shimotsukeno no Ason|qq=}} - Descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto, the son of Emperor Sujin * {{ill|Right Capital Ōno no Ason|ja|右京 大野朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Right Capital Ōno no Ason|qq=}} - Descendants of {{ill|Aratawake|ja|大荒田別命|Aratawake=Aratawake|lt=Ōaratawake-no-mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aratawake|qq=}}, the fourth-generation descendant of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto * {{ill|Left Capital Ikeda no Ason|ja|左京 池田朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Left Capital Ikeda no Ason|qq=}} - Same lineage as Kamitsukeno no Ason; descendants of Sada-kimi, the tenth-generation descendant of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto * {{ill|Right Capital Sami no Ason|ja|右京 佐味朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Right Capital Sami no Ason|qq=}} - Same lineage as Kamitsukeno no Ason; descendants of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto * {{ill|Left Capital Kuramochi no Ason|ja|左京 車持公|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Left Capital Kuramochi no Ason|qq=}} - Same lineage as Kamitsukeno no Ason; descendants of Isasa-kimi, the eighth-generation descendant of Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto
== References == {{reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|Kamitsukeno clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno clan|qq=}}
